        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I came across valid usecases some time ago which gave me 2 rows in a table with both the same username. Zend_Auth didn't like this, and gave me some ambiguity error. Imho Zend_Auth makes an assumption here that should be left up to the developer. Therefore I propose to add a flag by which the developer(s) can either disable or enable this check."
        },
