                    "created": "2009-07-16T04:11:41.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-16T04:11:41.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33497",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Can you supply some kind of script or api that demonstrates the issue?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-16T18:52:25.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-16T18:52:25.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36895",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=preinheimer",
                        "name": "preinheimer",
                        "displayName": "Paul Reinheimer",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Create a sample database.\r\nInsert two user accounts with the same username, but different passwords.\r\nAttempt to log in as one of them. \r\nAwait Error: \"More than one record matches the supplied identity.\"\r\n\r\nUsers of our system do not interact with each other, there's no reason to force username uniqueness. Yes, we are catching duplicate passwords :). \r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=preinheimer",
                        "name": "preinheimer",
                        "displayName": "Paul Reinheimer",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-13T20:13:20.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-13T20:13:20.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37733",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mabe",
                        "name": "mabe",
                        "displayName": "Marc Bennewitz (private)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "In my opinion this isn't something what Zend_Auth_Adapter_DbTable should implement.\r\n\r\nOne question:\r\nWhat message do you show if on user would like to change it's password to the same as one of the other users with the same name?\r\n->  Sorry, your given password is already defined by an other user. !??!?!?!?!?\r\n\r\n\r\nI think you have do write our own adapter (out of zf) if this functionality is a must have for you.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mabe",
                        "name": "mabe",
                        "displayName": "Marc Bennewitz (private)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-15T13:51:46.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-15T13:51:46.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37740",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "that's not the point, the point is that zend_auth shouldn't contrain me, at least not unoptionally (as of now, that is English).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-15T15:12:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-15T15:12:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41566",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dragonbe",
                        "name": "dragonbe",
                        "displayName": "Michelangelo van Dam",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "implemented this issue into the Zend_Auth_Adapter_DbTable.\r\n\r\nusage:\r\n{code:none}\r\n$authAdapter->setAmbiguityIdentity(true);\r\n{code}\r\n\r\ncan also be used fluently.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dragonbe",
                        "name": "dragonbe",
                        "displayName": "Michelangelo van Dam",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-17T06:51:28.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-17T06:51:28.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41567",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think that is best apply in Minor release.\r\nToo can be mentioned this feature in the manual.\r\n\r\nGreetings,\r\nRamon",
